I added in collect / concept / create to the Q deck to describe where we are now. <@U0ML49XU0> could you tell me whether we are still in collect or if we're officially in create now according to project schedule?
I'm hoping <@U0GN0A9EV> can fill in the concept slide, and <@U0ML49XU0> can fill in create. I think that's the complete deck we'll want to share at 2, unless you all have more you'd like to add.
I'm digging into it now
gonna dig in now as well
well, at noon
<@U0HP6TFNX> there is only Collect and Concept Phases of this project
I can work the existing content into this structure
should we do a slide that houses current questions/assumptions?
I thought Create would be a good spot to talk about our handoff to their team, which will be doing the create phase, and how we plan for touchpoints along the way
then you're thinking about it the right way <@U0HP6TFNX> that's exactly what i intend to do
i'll also throw in a questions/assumptions slide. <@U0HP6TFNX> plan is for you to walk thre group through it, with color commentary from me+ivan, right?
yes, that sounds good to me, I'll probably ask you / ivan to talk through the slides that you were the primary creator for
good good

<!channel> I want to include a slide in deck for client today with any BIG outstanding questions or assumptions. Please chime in with wha coms to mind for you. I have notes but I'd rather here from the team if there's anything on this

<@U0ML49XU0> there was conversation about gender on the memo re:FB.  to what extent do we consider gendered interactions as we craft the bot's voice? also, this leads us to the issue of personality as well.  they want the bot to be as concise as possible. but bots are useful insofar as they both solve a problem AND enhance experience. this suggests personality. is this something we engage client with?

<@U4VTSDW7P> i think so. I'd even be comfortable having a loosely structured dialog around this in the back half of our call; would you like that?  The goal of this call is to set us up in a manner that allows us to go heads down and execute ASAP so I want us to feel empowered to ask these questions now
yep. if there's time, this is fine. this set of questions is maybe less about going heads down and more about thought partnership:) so, we can deal with it later as well. it may put us off track.

i may have miscommunicated. Basically, I think if we blow through the deck in a short period of time, engaging with client on this question so that we can start formulating a plan or writing ASAP is in our best interest
not many other venues, outside of doing the writing and presenting, do we get to bring this up
Updated concept slide. please edit cause I don't talk words good

<!here|@here> last call on adding discussion point bullet points to the last page of the Q deck if you have lingering questions that need to be resolved before we can go heads down. We're sending in 7 minutes.

file.name: Analytics_Insights.txt
file.title: Analytics Insights
file.preview:
Inbox /Message Usage: Put this in the wishlist Google doc:
§  From the data, since the beginning of 2017, about 16.34% of returning member visits touched message or inbox pages. About 34.26% of returning members touched either pages. Most of the messages still happened on DT, about 41%. From the data, as the threads get longer, the % of messages which happened on DT decreased rather than increased. (This makes sense to me since I think they tend to reply back on any device available rather than just desktop.)
o    Triggers Answers: I think this is the best you will have to work with. Analytics didn’t give me any more than I could find, but I am pushing:
§  Seeker – we know most if they post a job (vs. enroll). If they posted a job:
·         1. what they are looking for
